A club member here in Fresno, Vince Corral,  is the original owner of a '67
HT Westy that has the brackets on the roof for the big tent, but has only
had the foyer tent.
Not sure of the M-codes, he'll be at BYOB and we can check them out. He's
easy to spot, velvet green with a Dormobile top that was installed in
Germany when he picked it up for a year long tour of Europe. It's been
completely resto'd with the unused brackets reinstalled and the same cracked
passenger windshield that appears in dozens of snapshots of the tour.

 -Harry in Fresno



